  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kwara State Eye Care Programme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of the project is to provide high quality comprehensive eye care services with full community participation and ownership by the state and local government to drastically reduce avoidable blindness.

The objectives include:
.
&#x2022; To have in place qualified manpower through training and retraining
&#x2022; To ensure state and local government are fully committed to the programme.
&#x2022; To ensure the provision of qualitative eye care services
&#x2022; To ensure community members are aware of the importance of eye health and demand for eye care services is created. 
&#x2022; To ensure the availability of appropriate infrastructure and consumables
Key activities include:
&#x2022; Advocacy,
&#x2022; Human resource development
&#x2022; Community sensitisation
&#x2022; Provision of equipment and consumables
&#x2022; Service delivery
&#x2022; Monitoring and evaluation

The aim is to contribute to poverty reduction through the prevention of avoidable blindness.</narrative>
  </description>
